==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tic
<hw>Tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A local and habitual convulsive motion of certain
muscles; especially, such a motion of some of the muscles of the face;
twitching; velication; -- called also <altname>spasmodic
tic</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tic douloureux</b></col> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>tic</ets> a knack, a twitching + <ets>douloureux</ets>
painful.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <cd>Neuralgia in the face; face ague.
See under <er>Face</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tical</ent>⟦br⟧
